  <AuthorByline lang="en" datePublished="2026-04-26" dateModified="2026-04-26" readingTime="11" />
</div>

<!-- INTRO: WHY UKRAINE IS UNDERESTIMATED MARKET -->
<section class="rze-intro">
  <div class="rze-intro__inner">
    <LabelChip text="01 · CONTEXT" variant="muted" />
    <h2 class="rze-h2">Ukraine is the most under-served large e-commerce market in Eastern Europe</h2>
    <p>Ukraine has 30 million online shoppers, the second-largest e-commerce GMV in Eastern Europe after Poland (≈ €11.2B in 2024 per Gemius), and the strongest year-over-year growth across the region (+18% in 2024 versus +9% Poland average). Despite the war, Ukrainian consumers spent €420 monthly per active online shopper in 2024 — higher than Romania and Bulgaria. The ratio of mobile-first commerce reached 67%, ahead of most EU markets. For international brands, this is a high-intent, under-supplied market that Western competitors have largely abandoned.</p>
    <p>Rozetka, the largest marketplace in Ukraine, runs an FBO (Fulfillment by Operator) program but excludes a long category list — oversized goods, large appliances, fragile glass without OEM packaging, supplements requiring cold chain, cosmetics with controlled temperature. Rozetka also charges 4-35% commission per sale plus ~3 EUR monthly platform fee — and locks the seller into a single channel. For brands building presence across Rozetka + Prom.ua + Kasta + their own DTC store, the FBO model is not viable.</p>
    <p>MTP Group offers an alternative: a single Ukraine-based fulfillment partner serving all those marketplaces from a unified inventory, with categories Rozetka FBO refuses, war-resilient infrastructure (zero downtime since 2022), 24-minute SLA, and direct EU dispatch via Nova Poshta International, Meest, DHL, and UPS. We are the operational backbone for 80+ brands entering Ukraine.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 4 PILLARS -->
<section class="rze-pillars">
  <div class="rze-pillars__inner">
    <LabelChip text="02 · 4 PILLARS" variant="muted" />
    <h2 class="rze-h2">4 pillars of multi-marketplace fulfillment in Ukraine</h2>
    <div class="rze-pillars__grid">
      <article class="rze-pillars__card">
        <span class="rze-pillars__num">01</span>
        <h3>Single inventory across 8+ channels</h3>
        <p>One stock count per SKU, distributed automatically to Rozetka, Prom.ua, Kasta, Allo, Bigl, Epicentr, OLX, your Shopify or Horoshop store. Marketplace-specific label formats printed on demand. No double-selling risk because the inventory is pooled, not duplicated.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rze-pillars__card">
        <span class="rze-pillars__num">02</span>
        <h3>Categories Rozetka FBO refuses</h3>
        <p>Oversized furniture, large appliances, fragile glass, supplements +2…+8°C, cold-chain cosmetics. We have 4 100 m² across 4 warehouses with separate climate zones, mobile equipment for oversized handling, multi-layer packaging for fragile, and 80+ brands in these categories.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rze-pillars__card">
        <span class="rze-pillars__num">03</span>
        <h3>EU dispatch without secondary handling</h3>
        <p>Nova Poshta International, Meest, DHL Express, UPS, FedEx — direct from our Kyiv-area warehouse. No 2-3 day delay through a Polish or Romanian consolidator hub, no €0.30-0.80 per parcel markup. For Allegro / Cdiscount / eBay DE dropship via Ukraine, this is operationally significant.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="rze-pillars__card">
        <span class="rze-pillars__num">04</span>
        <h3>War-resilient infrastructure</h3>
        <p>3 industrial generators (36-hour autonomy each), 5-day diesel reserve, 2 Starlink terminals, redundant fiber. Zero days of downtime since February 2022. During peak attacks on energy grid (winter 2022-2024), worst-day throughput drop was 8% — competitors lost 60-100%.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

